textBox.richText: People claim they see Heaven on Earth In some of the most beautiful and extravagant places In reality heaven is right before our eyes Some days heaven is a mystery, A shroud of wispy clouds are strewn across endless blue The sky protects our naivety and shields us from dangers, Like the warm protective wings of a mother bird but it also brings about a strong curiosity in mankind Everyone wants to see what utopia lays beyond the sheath of blue Or brilliant blanket of stars But somedays I’m content right where I am, Gazing across the horizon I’m in my own heaven on earth Why ask for more?
